rComments: TRN250 was a great class and overall, her teaching really did help expand my understanding of international relations. Lectures were content-heavy, but Ewing was very clearly passionate about the topic. My one critique: The TA's seemed like they were out to get us. My TA scrutinized every sentence in an assignment that was worth 10% of our grade.

rComments: Prof Ewing was an amazing prof to have. She is very passionate about the course and obviously cares very much about her students. She challenges you academically and goes through a lot of content every lecture so you have to work hard to do well. That being said she is one of my favourite professors and I'd take another course with her for sure.

Ewing is an absolute sweetheart - she's very passionate about history, as is reflected in her content-heavy, detail-oriented lecture style. She was also very always willing to help if needed. Only critique was the marking - very vague instructions, little communication between her and TAs. Easy to do decently, but very challenging to great

rComments: Prof Ewing is a real gem. It's rare that you get a prof at UofT who genuinely cares about their students, but she very clearly does. Lecture was a little unorganized and very content-heavy, but that's to be expected for a first-time lecturer. Be prepared to work hard.
